Before discussing the effect of scan rate, it is necessary to define a factor to quantify the degree of hysteresis. Several such factors have been defined in previous studies41,60. In this work, the hysteresis index (HI) is defined as:1HI=PCERS-PCEFSPCERS,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\begin{aligned} HI=\frac{PCE_{RS}-PCE_{FS}}{PCE_{RS}}~, \end{aligned}$$\end{document}where PCEFS\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
